canonical:
  title: 郊行
  author: 柳文通
  language: lzh
  text: 偸閑信馬過長堤兩岸春深草色齊江雨不知衣濕盡隔林茅店午時鷄
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 郊行
  author: 柳文通
  language: lzh
  text: 偸閑信馬過長堤。兩岸春深草色齊。江雨不知衣濕盡。隔林茅店午時鷄。
korean:
  title: 교행
  author: 유문통
  language: kor
  text: |-
    한가한 틈을 타서 말을 타고 긴 뚝을 지내나니
    양쪽 언덕에 봄은 깊어 푸른 풀이 가지런하다
    강 비에 옷이 다 젖는 줄을 알지 못하는데
    숲 넘어 주막집에 낮닭이 운다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0690&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Journey Beyond the City
  author: Yu Munong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Stealing away through the idle hours, I ride my horse along the long embankment.
    On both banks, spring runs deep—the grass grows verdant and even.
    In the river rain, I do not notice my robes soaked through,
    While from beyond the woods, a rooster crows at noon from a wayside inn.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'idle hours' (한가한 틈) suggest a stolen moment of freedom from official duties or social obligations, a common theme in classical East Asian poetry.
  - key: ''
    value: The description of grass growing 'even' (가지런하다) on both banks emphasizes the ordered beauty of spring and nature's harmony.
  - key: ''
    value: The rooster crowing at noon is unusual, as roosters typically crow at dawn; this detail suggests the poet's complete immersion in the journey and loss of ordinary time.
